    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ethiopian-style-cod-asa-wat-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail and chop your<strong> courgette[s]</strong> in half lengthways, then slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ethiopian-style-cod-asa-wat-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced courgette </strong>and <strong>diced onion </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until softened and starting to brown</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ethiopian-style-cod-asa-wat-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>ground turmeric </strong>to the pan with the<strong> chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>berbere seasoning </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong> and your<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has slightly thickened</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ethiopian-style-cod-asa-wat-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> into large, bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ethiopian-style-cod-asa-wat-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has slightly thickened, add the <strong>chopped fish </strong>to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 4-5 min further or until the fish is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>fish asa wat</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ethiopian-style-cod-asa-wat-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ethiopian-style-cod-asa-wat-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>fish asa wat</strong> with the <strong>cooked rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>sliced chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
